CliDriver.html.title: CliDriver
CliDriver.html.name: CliDriver
CliDriver.html.description: Usage example: const client = new Driver() client.start({cwd: /home/sg/myproject}) client.enter('ls') // now we wait until package.json is printed in stdout const data = await client.waitForData(data => data.includes('package.json'))

CliDriver.html#waitTimeout.description: for how long wait* function will wait until it return a rejected promise

CliDriver.html#waitInterval.title: waitInterval :number
CliDriver.html#waitInterval.name: waitInterval
CliDriver.html#waitInterval.description: how periodically wait* functions will poll to check given predicate

CliDriver.html#enter.name: enter
CliDriver.html#enter.description: Will write given text and then press ENTER

CliDriver.html#getDataFromLastWrite.name: getDataFromLastWrite
CliDriver.html#getDataFromLastWrite.description: get current data from last time enter() was issued
